The paper deals with the problem of learning labels for large text corpora, which is a common problem in machine learning and natural language processing. The proposed model is based on factorization of higher order moments, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and statistics. The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed algorithm, which is a common concern in large-scale machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
